==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mortmain
<hw>Mort"main`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mort</ets>, <ets>morte</ets>, dead + <ets>main</ets> hand; F.
<ets>main-morte</ets>. See <er>Mortal</er>, and <er>Manual</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Possession of lands or tenements in, or conveyance
to, dead hands, or hands that cannot alienate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term was originally applied to conveyance of land
made to ecclesiastical bodies; afterward to conveyance made to
<xex>any</xex> corporate body.</note> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mortmal</ent>⟦br⟧
